claim.claim-text:
8. A method for processing a substrate to be processed, comprising the steps of: 
forming on the substrate to be processed a photoresist layer for image formation not larger than 100 nm in thickness using the photoresist as set forth in claim 1; 
exposing the formed photoresist layer for image formation by means of near-field exposure; 
forming a pattern by developing the photoresist layer for image formation; and 
transferring the pattern formed on the photoresist layer onto the substrate.
